declarations.comments:
Contains a list of all the local files available on the data transfer.
Empty if the drag operation doesn't involve dragging files.

It's possible that a drag operation may have null files, instead of an
empty file list. In these cases Nothing is returned.
declarations.title: files

declarations.comments:
Returns an array of data formats used in the drag operation.
If the drag operation included no data, then the array is empty.
declarations.title: types

declarations.comments:
Retrieves the data for a given media type, or an empty string if data for
that type does not exist or the data transfer object contains no data.
declarations.title: getData

declarations.comments: Sets the data transfer object's data for a given media format.
declarations.title: setData

declarations.comments: Gets the data transfer object's drop effect.
declarations.title: dropEffect

declarations.comments: Sets the data transfer object's drop effect.
declarations.title: setDropEffect

declarations.comments:
Set timeout to `0` to get the same behaviour as when it is `undefined` in
[JavaScript](https://w3c.github.io/requestidlecallback/#h-the-requestidle-callback-method).
declarations.title: requestIdleCallback
